/sites/9/2023/05/Primoz-Roglic-wins-2023-Giro-dItalia-Massimo-Valicchia-NurPhoto-via-Getty-Image1-750x501.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/Primoz-Roglic-wins-2023-Giro-dItalia-Massimo-Valicchia-NurPhoto-via-Getty-Image1-1140x761.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/Primoz-Roglic-wins-2023-Giro-dItalia-Massimo-Valicchia-NurPhoto-via-Getty-Image1-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/Primoz-Roglic-wins-2023-Giro-dItalia-Massimo-Valicchia-NurPhoto-via-Getty-Image1-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/Primoz-Roglic-wins-2023-Giro-dItalia-Massimo-Valicchia-NurPhoto-via-Getty-Image1-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Massimo Valicchia/NurPhoto via Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Eurosport/Discovery</strong>: Pan-Europe (including UK), Asia-Pacific (excluding China) and Indian subcontinent</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>FloSports/FloBikes</strong>: Canada, Australia</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>BeIn Sport &amp; Max:</strong> USA</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Claro+ &amp; DirecTV</strong>: Latin America &amp; Caribbean</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>SBS: </strong>Australia</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>La Chaîne L’Équipe:</strong> France</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>RTBF &amp; VRT</strong>: Belgium</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>RAI</strong>: Italy, San Marino, Vatican City</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>NOS</strong>: Netherlands</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>EITB: </strong>Basque Country</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>S4C:</strong> Wales</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>J Sports:</strong> Japan</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>SRG-SSR</strong>: Switzerland</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Starzsport</strong>: Middle East (including Malta and Israel)</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Zhibo.tv</strong>: China</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Supersport</strong>: Sub-Saharan Africa (including South Africa)</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Find all our Giro d’Italia co